lead_paragraph: On Aug. 3, 1776, another Spitfire let go its guns in the cause of liberty. It was a Spitfire on this side of the Atlantic and it had wings of canvas, not metal, but its task was the same as the R.A.F. fighter plane's today, to make tyranny tremble and let freedom ring.
